# Complete unit-test coverage for all clautolisp builtins

Status: open
Baseline: master @ 0a45e4b (clautolisp 1.0.70 + missing-functions
landed + the M2-M5 coverage backfill)

## Goal

Bring every implemented AutoLISP operator under a focused FiveAM
unit test. Today's coverage is 65% behavioural / 80% any-mention.
Target: 100% any-mention, ≥ 95% behavioural (the 5% slack covers
host-coupled families whose meaningful test is a MockHost
scenario, not a builtin unit test).

## Current state (measured 2026-05-26)

Methodology: extract every name registered via
`make-core-builtin-subr` + the special-operator dispatch table
(the implemented set), then cross-reference against names
appearing in:

  * FiveAM test snippets — names as form heads inside
    `run-autolisp-string` calls in
    `clautolisp/autolisp-builtins-core/tests/builtin-tests.lisp`
    and `clautolisp/autolisp-runtime/tests/evaluator-tests.lisp`.
  * Bulk registration sweeps — names as bare strings in CL
    `dolist` lists (the `m3d-vle-all-stubs-registered` /
    `m4-vlisp-*` / `m5-*` group tests assert "binds a SUBR" but
    don't actually call the function).
  * Scenario corpus — `.sexp` files under `autolisp-test/tests/`
    and `autolisp-front-end/tests/scenarios/`.

| Metric | Count | % of 578 |
|--------|------:|---------:|
| Implemented (core builtins + special ops) | 578 | 100% |
| Behavioural coverage (called from a test snippet)         | 379 | 65.6% |
| Registration-only (in a `dolist`, never called)           |  88 | 15.2% |
| Any test mention                                          | 467 | 80.8% |
| **Genuinely untested**                                    | **111** | **19.2%** |

## Acceptance criteria

  * Every of the 111 genuinely-untested operators gains at least
    one FiveAM test that invokes it from an AutoLISP snippet and
    asserts the result (not just `(is (not (null result)))` —
    the test should pin down the documented return value or a
    specific structural property).
  * Every of the 88 registration-only operators gains at least
    one behavioural test. For pure stubs that documentation says
    return nil, that's a single-line `(is (null …))` check —
    fine. The point is to exercise the call path, not just the
    registry.
  * The coverage-measurement script above (or a moral
    equivalent) is checked in as
    `autolisp-builtins-core/tests/scripts/coverage-report.sh` so
    the next regression is caught.
  * builtins-core suite count climbs to ~1100+ checks (from 817
    today); every other suite stays 100% green.

## Genuinely untested — by family

Total: 111. Grouped by natural batch shape.

== Cxxr accessors (14) ==

CAAADR CAADAR CAADDR CADAAR CADADR CADDAR CDAAAR CDAADR CDADAR
CDADDR CDDAAR CDDADR CDDDAR CDDDDR

One test per accessor verifying the right car/cdr chain on a
nested list. The existing `builtin-caxr-family` test spot-checks
a few; extend to the full set. Trivial — ~20 lines total.

== DCL dialog / tile / image / list builtins (14) ==

ADD_LIST CLIENT_DATA_TILE DIMX_TILE DIMY_TILE END_IMAGE END_LIST
FILL_IMAGE MODE_TILE SLIDE_IMAGE START_IMAGE START_LIST
TERM_DIALOG UNLOAD_DIALOG VECTOR_IMAGE

These work against the autolisp-dcl test fixture. Pattern: open
a small dialog, drive a tile / image / list operation, assert
the resulting state. Look at the existing `runtime-set-and-get-
tile-roundtrip` test in `autolisp-dcl-suite` for the shape.

== Interactive prompts (GET* / INITGET) (11) ==

GETANGLE GETCORNER GETDIST GETINT GETKWORD GETORIENT GETPOINT
GETREAL GETSTRING GETVAR INITGET

The `autolisp-mock-host-suite` already exercises these against
MockHost via mocked input streams. The BUILTIN side just
delegates to the host; the gap is that builtins-core has no
matching tests. Either:
  (a) Add thin builtins-core tests asserting the delegation
      shape (the call reaches the active host with the right
      arg shape), OR
  (b) Move the coverage-counting goalpost — mark these as
      "tested via mock-host suite" and exempt from
      builtins-core's count.

Option (a) is the cleaner answer; pick that.

== Selection-set + entity DB ops (9) ==

ENTDEL ENTMAKEX ENTUPD SSADD SSDEL SSGETFIRST SSMEMB SSNAME
SSSETFIRST TBLOBJNAME

Same situation as GET* — covered indirectly via the mock-host
suite's pickset / entity tests. Backfill builtins-core
delegation-shape tests.

== VLAX-* (8) ==

VLAX-GET-OR-CREATE-OBJECT VLAX-METHOD-APPLICABLE-P
VLAX-PROPERTY-AVAILABLE-P VLAX-SAFEARRAY-GET-L-BOUND
VLAX-SAFEARRAY-GET-U-BOUND VLAX-SAFEARRAY-PUT-ELEMENT
VLAX-SAFEARRAY-TYPE VLAX-VARIANT-CHANGE-TYPE

ActiveX/COM surface. Covered indirectly by mock-host VLAX tests;
backfill builtins-core spot-checks.

== VLE-NTH shortcuts (7) ==

VLE-NTH1 VLE-NTH2 VLE-NTH4 VLE-NTH5 VLE-NTH6 VLE-NTH7 VLE-NTH8
VLE-SET-CDRASSOC

The `m3a-vle-nth-shortcuts` test covers NTH0, NTH3, NTH9 as
representatives. Extend to the rest of the family for symmetry
(or move to a `:test-all-nths` macro that generates one is per
index). VLE-SET-CDRASSOC needs a dedicated test asserting the
mutation.

== VLR-* reactors (~40) ==

VLR-ACDB-REACTOR VLR-ADDED-P VLR-CURRENT-REACTION-NAME VLR-DATA
VLR-DEEPCLONE-REACTOR VLR-DOCMANAGER-REACTOR VLR-DOCUMENT-REACTOR
VLR-DWG-REACTOR VLR-DXF-REACTOR VLR-INSERT-REACTOR
VLR-LINKER-REACTOR VLR-LISP-REACTOR VLR-MISCELLANEOUS-REACTOR
VLR-MOUSE-REACTOR VLR-NOTIFICATION VLR-OWNER-ADD VLR-OWNER-REMOVE
VLR-OWNERS VLR-PERS VLR-PERS-DICTNAME VLR-PERS-LIST VLR-PERS-P
VLR-PERS-RELEASE VLR-REACTION-SET VLR-REACTIONS VLR-REACTORS
VLR-REMOVE-ALL VLR-SET-NOTIFICATION VLR-SYSVAR-REACTOR
VLR-TOOLBAR-REACTOR VLR-TRACE-REACTION VLR-TYPE VLR-TYPES
VLR-UNDO-REACTOR VLR-WBLOCK-REACTOR VLR-WINDOW-REACTOR
VLR-XREF-REACTOR

These were registered as part of the pre-missing-functions work
(VLR-REACTORS, VLR-* family). They exist on the BUILTIN side but
have no FiveAM tests. The reactor-fires-on-mock-host-mutation
test in the mock-host suite covers the dispatch; backfill
builtins-core unit tests for the predicate/accessor surface.

== Misc one-offs (8) ==

1+ 1- ~ DOC_CLIPBOARD STARTAPP SETFUNHELP VL-BT _VLAX-SAFEARRAY-MODE

  * 1+, 1- — covered indirectly via arithmetic tests but lack
    direct tests. Add one each.
  * ~ — bitwise NOT; covered via the arithmetic family test but
    no direct test exists.
  * DOC_CLIPBOARD — smoke-tested manually but no FiveAM. Add a
    test that uses pbpaste/pbcopy roundtrip when available
    (`#+darwin` reader conditional) and skips on other platforms.
  * STARTAPP — covered by VLE-STARTAPP's test via aliasing? No,
    different code path. Add a test that launches `/usr/bin/true`
    and asserts the PID return.
  * SETFUNHELP — Visual LISP help-string registrar; add a stub
    test that calls it and asserts T return.
  * VL-BT — backtrace dump; covered manually but no FiveAM.
  * _VLAX-SAFEARRAY-MODE — internal ActiveX policy flag; add a
    nil-return test.

## Registration-only — by family

Total: 88. These already have a `is (typep subr 'autolisp-subr)`
assertion via the bulk M3d/M4/M5 sweep tests. The gap is
behavioural coverage. Most return documented nil/T; a one-line
`(is (null (run-autolisp-string "(foo …)")))` per function
suffices.

