## Suggested execution

One PR per family, smallest first so each lands quickly:

  1. Cxxr accessors (14) — half an hour
  2. VLE-NTH1..8 + SET-CDRASSOC (8) — half an hour
  3. Misc one-offs (8) — half an hour
  4. VL-LOCAL-UNDO-* + VL-SUBENT-* + VL-VPLAYER-* + VL-ANNOTATIVE-*
     (24, all nil-return stubs) — one hour
  5. VLE-* CAD/COM/UI stubs (20) — one hour
  6. Cxxr-style sweep over the GET* / SS* / ENT* / TBL* /
     VLAX-SAFEARRAY-* / VLR-* families (~70) — three hours, plus
     a chunk of head-down work figuring out the right delegation
     assertions for each.

Total: half a day of focused work; reaches >95% behavioural
coverage. The coverage-report.sh script lands in step 1 so each
subsequent PR shows the delta in the commit message.

## Out of scope

  * Spec-conformance vendor probes (those live in
    `deferred-spec-research.issue`).
  * Stub-to-real promotion of any of the 88 register-only
    entries (those live in `deferred-stubbed-functions.issue`).
    This issue is strictly about test coverage.
  * The 411 still-missing operators tracked in
    `missing-functions.issue` — they don't exist yet, so they
    can't be tested. (Closes naturally as those families land.)
